13/04/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Officials announced on Wednesday (12 April) that Turkey has decided to build its first nuclear power plant at Sinop, on the Black Sea. A pilot project involving the construction of a small 100-megawatt reactor is expected to begin in early 2007. 
In other news, Turkey said it would expel a British human rights monitor for alleged visa violations. Jonathan Sugden, who works for Human Rights Watch, was arrested in Bingol where he was investigating alleged abuses against Kurds. 
On Tuesday meanwhile, 14 people -- two Turkish soldiers and 12 Kurdish militants -- were killed in new fighting between the army and members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party in southeast Turkey. (Reuters, Turks.US - 12/04/06)
